sql:
SELECT * 
FROM notifications 
WHERE user_id = (SELECT author_id FROM authors WHERE author_name = 'Olga Caprotti');

SELECT p.project_id, p.title, a.author_name, p.description
FROM projects p
LEFT JOIN authors a ON p.author_id = a.author_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'key explorers' refers to users whose role is 'researcher'.;
- 'academic journey' is a metaphor for projects.;
- 'titles of their voyages' represent the titles of the projects led by the researchers. ;
- 'ship's log' is a metaphor for notifications related to the researcher's work. ;
- 'messages they have acknowledged' signify notifications they have read. ;
- 'harbors they are visiting' metaphorically represents the events associated with the projects. ;
- 'latest departure of their voyages' refers to the start date of the projects sorted in descending order.

- "initial project" refers to the project with project ID 0;
- "folks" refers to the users in the system;
- "not involved" means the users whose IDs do not appear in the project access records for the specified project.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name, u.email 
FROM users u
JOIN event_registrations e ON u.user_id = e.user_id;

SELECT DISTINCT title
FROM projects
WHERE visibility = 'public';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS Sticky_Posts_Count
FROM discussion_posts
WHERE is_sticky = 1;

SELECT projects.title, authors.author_name 
FROM projects 
INNER JOIN authors ON projects.author_id = authors.author_id;

SELECT version_number
FROM project_versions
WHERE project_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Active projects are those that are currently ongoing;
Resources in use are those that are being currently utilized by the project;
Recent events refer to those that have taken place within the last 12 months.
